  reset/recovery cleanup layer.                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                
  A later live Slack test showed that sessions.reset by itself was not enough in the already-poisoned channel case. The                                         
  reset moved the Slack channel binding to a fresh session id, but the old in-memory embedded-run/lane state still                                              
  appeared to own the queue. Three later Slack messages were accepted but did not get replies; diagnostics showed:                                              
                                                                                                                                                                
